### 🐛 Summary of Bugs Found

| # | Bug | Severity | Location |
|---|-----|----------|----------|
| 1 | **Filter input does not filter list items** - typing any keyword in the filter input has no effect on the displayed list | **Critical** | Basic Filter section |
| 2 | **OptGroups filter input does not filter list items** - same issue as above for grouped options | **Critical** | Filter with OptGroups section |

### Root Cause Analysis
The filter feature (`filter: true`) appears to render the search input UI correctly (input box with search icon is visible), but the **event listener or filtering logic is not connected to the input field**. When text is typed, the input value changes but no filtering action is triggered on the list items. This affects both plain lists and optgroup-structured lists equally.
